  abstract =	 {The expected number of secondary cases produced by a
                  typical infected individual during its entire period
                  of infectiousness in a completely susceptible
                  population is mathematically defined as the dominant
                  eigenvalue of a positive linear operator. It is
                  shown that in certain special cases one can easily
                  compute or estimate this eigenvalue. Several
                  examples involving various structuring variables
                  like age, sexual disposition and activity are
                  presented.}
